Here is the spatial data and architectural framework to map your chronological lifeline directly onto a geographical engine. Since you are building out this integration—and to match your cognitive topology—the framework below is structured using a GeoJSON schema.You can directly copy this data payload, save it as a .geojson file, and import it straight into Google My Maps, Google Earth, or use it as a database source for a custom Google Maps JavaScript API build.1. Geospatial Coordinate ManifestNode IDLocation / LandmarkTarget Coordinates (Lat, Lon)Chrono-WindowKey Textures & Metadata01Snohomish Birthplace / Farm47.9129° N, 122.0982° WAug 1983 – 1986Root node. Native cedar canopy, alluvial farm soil.02Everett Residence (Lowell Neighborhood)47.9535° N, 122.1880° W1986 – 19913-story house, elevated view of BNSF tracks/river.03Lowell Elementary Playground47.9547° N, 122.1895° W1986 – 1991Heavy timber tree-to-tree bridge, interior tree slide.04I-5 Freeway Underpass (Lowell-Larimer)47.9575° N, 122.1932° WLate 1980sConcrete spatial stress-test pathway. Acoustic compression.05Summerhill Pointe Apartments (The Lakes)36.1432° N, 115.3032° W1991 – 1992+9501 W Sahara Ave. 2nd-floor tier vantage node.06Challenger School / Elementary (Vegas)36.1411° N, 115.2985° W1991+Academic acceleration zone. Post-Challenger naming era.07Luxor Foundation Footprint36.0956° N, 115.1758° WMid 1992Raw poured concrete base, un-framed pyramid plane.08MGM Grand Original Entrance36.1027° N, 115.1699° WMid 1992Physical 75-ft emerald/gold lion head portal.2. Ingestion-Ready GeoJSON Data FrameworkThis code block contains the structural nodes of your life history map. It links geographical polygon/point layers to absolute time stamps (timestamp) to prevent any disruption to your thinking topology.JSON{
