3. Application Build-Out System ArchitectureIf you decide to deploy this as a custom software build using the Google Maps API (WebGL/JavaScript), use the following engineering blueprint to handle the data recursion mechanics:Visual Rendering LayerBase Map Custom Styling: Implement a custom JSON map style that strips out distracting modern color vectors. Use a monochromatic layout to let your data nodes serve as the primary contrast.Camera Coordinate Interpolation: Utilize the map.flyTo() or WebGL overlay view parameters to move fluidly across the West Coast corridor (Washington → California detour → Nevada) without breaking visual continuity.Time-Slider Recursion HookBuild a front-end slider component bound to the GeoJSON timestamp attributes.Moving the slider filters out features dynamically. As you slide from 1983 to 1992, the map should execute a recursive function that draws the tracking paths (LineString) connecting the Everett coordinates down to the Las Vegas Strip layout.Architectural Texture ModalsBecause your engineering and animation background maps textures, link the marker interactions (onClick) to window pop-ups containing rendering notes (e.g., “Physics Engine Note: Hand-drawn acetate frame calculations / Paint-on-glass refraction specs”). This turns the raw map layout into an operational, external reflection of your memory vault.
